libargon2
------------------------------------------
Argon2 is a password-hashing function that summarizes the state of the art in
the design of memory-hard functions and can be used to hash passwords for
credential storage, key derivation, or other applications.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1
  cygwin-devel-2.11.2-1
  libargon2-devel-20171227-1bl1
  libargon2_1-20171227-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/P-H-C/phc-winner-argon2

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/P-H-C/phc-winner-argon2/archive/20171227.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libargon2-20171227-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libargon2-20171227-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libargon2-20171227-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libargon2-20171227-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libargon2_1-20171227-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libargon2-devel-20171227-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libargon2)
  /usr/bin/argon2.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libargon2.README
  /usr/share/doc/libargon2/ChangeLog.md
  /usr/share/doc/libargon2/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libargon2/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/libargon2/argon2-specs.pdf
  /usr/share/man/man1/argon2.1.gz

(libargon2_1)
  /usr/bin/cygargon2-1.dll

(libargon2-devel)
  /usr/include/argon2.h
  /usr/lib/libargon2.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libargon2.pc

